Package utils.exceptions

package utils.exceptions
This package contains the exceptions that are thrown by the application.
  • Exception Classes
    Class
    Description
    ModelAlreadyExistsException
    The ModelAlreadyExistsException class is a custom exception that is thrown when an attempt is made to add a model to a Database that already contains a model with the same ID.
    ModelNotFoundException
    The ModelNotFoundException class is a custom exception that is thrown when a requested model cannot be found in a Database.
    PageBackException
    The PageBackException class is a custom exception that is thrown when a user attempts to navigate back from a UI page where it is not allowed.
    PasswordDoesNotFulfilCriteriaException
    The PasswordDoesNotFulfilCriteriaException class is a custom exception that is thrown when a password does not fulfill the required criteria.
    PasswordIncorrectException
    The PasswordIncorrectException class is a custom exception that is thrown when an incorrect password is entered.
    UserAlreadyExistsException
    The UserAlreadyExistsException class is a custom exception that is thrown when attempting to create a user that already exists.
    UserCannotBeFoundException
    The UserCannotBeFoundException class is a custom exception that is thrown when a specified user cannot be found in the system.
